A family at Korinda Estate on the outskirts of Busia town is living in agony following the mysterious disappearance of their son two weeks ago. 14-year old, Eugine Peter Obiilo who is also a Standard 8 candidate at Mundika Boys Primary School went missing on September 5. Family members say he left home for a nearby church as was usual but never returned. The family is appealing to anyone who may have knowledge of the whereabouts of the boy to release him. The relatives say Obilo needs to be preparing for his KCPE exam slated for March next year. A missing person report has also been filed at Busia Police Station under OB number 68/6/9/2021A  Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam